title: Known Prairie Remnants on Publicly-Owned Lands, Iowa, 2004
name: Known Prairie Remnants on Publicly-Owned Lands, Iowa, 2004
description:
Abstract:

Locations of known remnant prairies on public land.

Purpose:

The data set was developed to allow users to locate remnant prairies on public lands.  This digital, geographically referenced data set was developed by the Iowa Department of Natural Resources to carry out agency responsibilities related to management, protection, and development of Iowa's natural resources.

Supplemental_Information:

Data represent locations of remnant prairies reported to the DNR by numerous individuals and organizations.  Though efforts have been made to include only accurate information, it has not been possible to field verify the reported sites.   Boundaries are approximate only.  Users of the data should follow signage posted on site to avoid trespassing.
